{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, we found two types of dimensionality reduction and feature selection algorithms: Principal Component Analysis (PCA), and Manifold Learning which includes the Isomap Algorithm used by Chaby et al. (2017), and t-distributed Stochastic Neighbor Embedding (t-SNE) used by Król and Król (2019).",
    "Figure 10 shows the distribution of the unsupervised learning algorithms with respect to the five research domains.",
    "Psychology and Education were the main research domains to use unsupervised learning.",
    "PCA was the most common unsupervised learning algorithm and the only one used by all five research domains.",
    "We can see that both Partitioning and Hierarchical Clustering were more popular than Density-Based and Grid-Based Clustering."
  ]
}